children.text: The balcony waterproofing has not been adequately installed high enough up the walls/vertical surfaces, which may result in water leaking.
Part 3.8.1.3 - External above ground membranes of the NCC’s Building Code of Australia requires that
‘Waterproofing membranes for external above ground use must comply with AS 4654.1 and AS 4654.2’
, and the relevant Australian Standard AS 4654.2 Waterproofing membranes for external above-ground use in Clause 2.8.1 – Upward terminations states that

‘Where the membrane is to prevent water entry, the finished height of the membrane above the finished surface level shall be sufficient to prevent water, including wind driven, flowing over the top of the membrane’ .
This balcony will need to be properly waterproofed the correct vertical upward termination height above the finished floor height, in accordance with the BCA and AS 4654.
